##### 2010 Census Data

According to the [2010 census](/2010_United_States_census), &#91;33&#93; Gates County was home to 12,197 people. The county contained 3,901 households, with 2,933 of these classified as families. The [population density](/Population_density) was approximately 31 people per square mile (12 people/km 2 ). There were 4,389 housing units, resulting in an average density of 13 units per square mile (5.0 units/km 2 ).

The racial makeup of the county at that time was:
